<Author>MicheleD79
<Content>Absolutely lovely hotel My sister and her boyfriend live in Berlin and booked this hotel for our parents when we came to visit them (I stayed at their place). They booked the Honigmond because it looked lovely when they had passed there once and it was just 2 streets away from their home. My parents are used to very high standard hotels and service and were absolutely very satisfied with this hotel.The location is superb, in a very quiet street just 5 minutes walking from the galleries and little shops of Mitte and not even 5 min walking from the Nordbahnhof metro station.The reception area is just lovely, with leather chairs, tables with travel guides and newspapers, a bowl full of lovely chocolates, chocolates at the reception, a free internet pc, etc.The staff is very friendly and helpful as well.Rooms are just adorable, with four-poster beds, charming decoration and ceiling ornaments, and an impeccable bathroom. Only downside perhaps is that the rooms are not extremely big and there was no place to put the suitcase on.Breakfast is excellent and plentyful, including some brunch items. The 3 of us went to have breakfast with my parents, and it was just 8,50鈧?each + drinks. One downside: no fresh orange juice.All in all a great experience ! 
