<Author>AngloTexan
<Content>A great base for exploring Berlin We stayed at the Honigmond for a few days in April while we explored Berlin. Good location within walking distance of a bunch of the sights and with a number of public transport options close by. Great room, spacious and clean, cool decor! The staff were friendly and helpful. Breakfast was awesome: the best breakfast / brunch buffet I have come across so far! We did not have dinner in the hotel restaurant as there a few good restaurants close to the hotel (Sarah Weiner, the Restaurant in the Brechthaus). Can't think of anything bad to say about this hotel! 
