<Author>HampshireElizabethR
<Content>Great Berlin experience We booked this on the strength of other reviews and were not disappointed. With only a couple of weeks notice the hotel could only offer an apartment: this gave us slight over-capacity but we were very pleased with the rooms, which were extremely spacious, clean and stylish. The staff were polite and helpful (although not altogether fluent in English). The hotel was well-situated for our interests, which mainly lay in the museums. Moreover, we found the immediate surroundings fairly quiet and nice to escape to after the bustle of the city centre. Breakfast was superb - we have never seen such a spread! The restaurant, although (we are told) under different management, is well worth it, with particularly large portions. All in all, an excellent stay. We hope to be back sometime. 
