<Author>SantaFeB
<Content>East Berlin Beauty The Honigmond (honey moon in literally translated German) Hotel in Berlin Mitte is a jewel. Its great location, great staff, great rooms and a fabulous restaurant make a stay at the Honigmond a memorable one. The included breakfast is extensive enough to fill you up 'til dinner. The rooms are individually decorated -- check out several of them before you choose because a few (not many) share a bath. (None of the rooms, as far as I could tell, have phones in them.) But the bathrooms are spotless and modern, the flat screen TV's are perfect for watching CNN, and in the comfortable lobby a computer provides free Internet access for all guests. The Honigmond is within easy walking distance to U-Bahn and S-Bahn stations and to many Strassenbahn (streetcar) and bus lines, AND within walking distance to a large group of outstanding restaurants AND within walking distance to the best of Berlin's cutting edge art galleries. From the hotel it's a short cab ride to Tegel, still Berlin's primary airport. I'd bed down again at the Honigmond in a heartbeat. 
